A receiver method is a function called through a value.

Its first parameter is named `this`:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Vector2 = |
        x Float,
        y Float,
    |

    length_squared |this Vector2| -> Float:
        return this.x * this.x + this.y * this.y
    ;

    vector = Vector2(3.0, 4.0)
    length = vector.length_squared()
]

The method is written as a normal top-level function in the same file as the
type.

Call it with `value.method()`, not `method(value)`.
